comments: Nance Jr. (NOP) brushes Reaves' (LAL) right arm and marginal contact occurs after Reaves retrieves the loose ball.
Graham (NOP) avoids making contact with Reaves' (LAL) arm as the play moves in transition.
Graham (NOP) is drifting toward the middle of the lane and marginal body contact occurs with Davis (LAL) after Davis receives the pass.
Murphy III (NOP) makes clean contact with the ball and dislodges it away from Davis (LAL) in the lane.
Marshall (NOP) immediately slides his hand off of James' (LAL) side and marginal contact occurs during the inbound.
Murphy III (NOP) touches the ball last before it goes out of bounds.
Williamson (NOP) is in the paint for longer than three seconds without imminently actively guarding an opponent.
Nance Jr. (NOP) initiates contact across James' (LAL) right arm and affects his driving shot attempt.
Beverley (LAL) makes clean contact with the ball and dislodges it away from Marshall (NOP) prior to any incidental contact occurring during rebounding.
Nance Jr. (NOP) moves underneath Reaves (LAL) and initiates body contact that causes Reaves to become dislodged during rebounding.
McCollum (NOP) and Beverley (LAL) make incidental foot-to-foot contact with one another off-ball.
Reaves (LAL) makes contact with the ball and the part of Williamson's (NOP) hand that is on the ball as simultaneous marginal contact occurs with Williamson's side after his gather.
Davis (LAL) brings his right hand toward Marshall's (NOP) back and marginal contact occurs as Davis releases away to roll.
Marshall (NOP) makes clean contact with the ball as simultaneous marginal contact occurs with James' (LAL) front as he makes the pass.
Marshall (NOP) rests his hands on Davis' (LAL) back and releases away as marginal contact occurs when Davis elevates for the rebound.
Marshall (NOP) rests his forearm on Davis' (LAL) side and marginal contact occurs as Davis is attempting the put-back.
James (LAL) initiates contact across Williamson's (NOP) arms during his upward shooting motion and affects the jump shot attempt.
Williamson (NOP) is in the paint for less than three seconds when he could be deemed to be imminently actively guarding Davis (LAL).
Nance Jr. (NOP) legally contests James' (LAL) jump shot attempt.
Davis (LAL) and Williamson (NOP) engage and disengage with one another during rebounding.

Reaves (LAL) brushes McCollum's (NOP) left arm and marginal contact occurs as McCollum starts his dribble. Simultaneously, Walker IV (LAL) brings his hands toward McCollum's path and marginal contact occurs with McCollum's front.
McCollum (NOP) engages and disengages with Beverley (LAL) during the inbound.
Murphy III (NOP) legally contests Walker IV's (LAL) jump shot attempt.
Davis (LAL) initiates contact with Daniels' (NOP) arm and side as he returns to the floor following the rebound.
Ryan (LAL) gathers the pass on his right foot and takes two steps before starting his upward shooting motion.
Ryan (LAL) remains in-bounds after receiving the pass in the corner.
Davis (LAL) re-establishes slightly in Marshall's (NOP) path after the initial contact during the screen and further marginal contact occurs simultaneously with the defensive switch.
Murphy III (NOP) legally contests Ryan's (LAL) jump shot attempt. After communicating with the Replay Center, the on-court ruling of a successful three point field goal was confirmed.
Nance Jr. (NOP) is established in James' (LAL) path and absorbs the marginal body contact that occurs as James ends his dribble inside the lane.
James (LAL) gathers the ball on his right foot and establishes his left foot as his pivot, which he lifts and re-plants before starting his upward shooting motion.

Nance Jr.'s (NOP) left arm comes down slightly and marginal contact occurs with the top of James' (LAL) head during James' upward shooting motion. Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Reaves (LAL) legally contests Murphy III's (NOP) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Williamson (NOP) brushes Davis' (LAL) left leg and simultaneous marginal contact occurs with Davis' left side after he retrieves the rebound.
Beverley (LAL) brings his hand/forearm toward Marshall's (NOP) back as he sets the pick and marginal contact occurs as Beverley releases away.

McCollum (NOP) makes clean contact with the ball prior to marginal contact occurring with Walker IV's (LAL) left leg after his gather. McCollum then elevates and cleanly blocks the driving shot attempt.
James (LAL) does not release the jump shot attempt prior to the expiration of the shot clock. Correctly called shot clock violation on LAL.
McCollum (NOP) touches the ball last before it goes out of bounds.
James (LAL) and Marshall (NOP) engage and disengage with one another during the inbound.
Beverley (LAL) briefly has his arms around Williamson's (NOP) midsection before quickly releasing.
Beverley (LAL) maintains a rested forearm on McCollum's (NOP) side and marginal contact occurs after McCollum's gather. Beverley then avoids making contact with McCollum as he elevates thereafter.
Williamson (NOP) makes contact with the ball and the part of Davis' (LAL) hand that is on the ball, dislodging it away prior to him or Nance Jr. (NOP) making incidental contact with Davis thereafter.
James (LAL) makes clean contact with the ball and dislodges it away from Nance Jr. (NOP) prior to incidental contact occurring.
James (LAL) touches the ball last before it goes out of bounds.
Nance Jr. (NOP) firms up on his left foot as he establishes himself in Reaves's (LAL) path and Nance Jr. does not deliver illegal contact.
Beverley (LAL) is moving forward toward the sideline when marginal body contact occurs with Nance Jr. (NOP) as he pivots.
Walker IV (LAL) establishes himself in Marshall's (NOP) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Davis (LAL) and Nance Jr. (NOP) mutually engage and disengage with one another after the release of the jump shot attempt.
Beverley (LAL) avoids making contact with McCollum (NOP) and legally contests the jump shot attempt.
Nance Jr. (NOP) and Davis (LAL) each jump toward one another as they pursue the loose ball and marginal body contact occurs.
